He said he had not spoken to Mr Cameron about the issue or the potential recall of Parliament. 

Britain was caught flat-footed yesterday when the US carried out its first air strikes on IS positions in Syria, in conjunction with five Arab countries.

Downing Street is understood to have been given a 'courtesy call' by the Pentagon shortly beforehand.

But the UK was notably absent from a list of allies praised by Barack Obama yesterday for standing 'shoulder to shoulder' with the US.

